cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for disambiguating word forms in inflected lexicons. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses unsupervised learning and neural networks, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses evaluation metrics and reports results, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
